The '''Blackwell–Tapia Prize''' is a [[mathematics]] award presented every other year at the Blackwell-Tapia conference. The conference is sponsored by the [[National Science Foundation]] and is organized and hosted by various mathematics institutes. The prize is named for [[David Blackwell]] and [[Richard Tapia]].<ref name=mathinstitutes>{{cite web |url=https://mathinstitutes.org/diversity/blackwell-tapia-conference/ |title=Blackwell-Tapia Conference and Award Ceremony |access-date=16 January 2018 |website=[[National Science Foundation]]}}</ref> It recognizes someone who has made significant research contributions in their field, and who has worked to address the problem of under-representation of minority groups in mathematics.<ref name = "vazquez">{{cite web |url=http://www.nimbios.org/wordpress/2016/04/13/vazquez-to-receive-2016-blackwell-tapia-prize/ |title=Vazquez to Receive 2016 Blackwell–Tapia Prize |website=[[NIMBioS]] |date=13 April 2016 |access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref>
